Europe's only research institute with a library and an archive for the literature and culture of the world of employment. For the first time in its 80-year history, a comprehensive inventory of the holdings of the library and manuscript, document, graphic, media and photographic archives is available. The main focus is on the lyrics and biographies of employees and unemployed people from 1800 to the present, complete archives of different author associations, authors bequests as well as collections of cultural organizations. Comprehensive indexes of names, places and subjects make it possible to find individual entries quickly.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aLabor. 0aWork. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Museum Administration & Museology.2bisacsh1 aNoltenius, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoltenius, Rainer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPalm, Hanneliese, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalm, Hanneliese, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVogt, Gregor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVogt, Gregor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LIBRARY AND INFORMATION SCIENCE  2005z9783110276916oZDB-23-DGB0 cprintz978359811199040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311097042540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110970425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110970425/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGA